Sentencas: Chemical compatibility and cation interdiffusion between the double perovskite cobaltites RBaCo2O6-delta (R = Gd, Pr) and proton-conducting electrolyte BaZr0.8Y0.2O3-delta were studied.
Titulo: Implications of Cation Interdiffusion between Double Perovskite Cathode and Proton-Conducting Electrolyte for Performance of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Chemical interaction was found to occur already at 1100 degrees C as a result of the partial dissolution of RBaCo2O6-delta (R = Gd, Pr) in BaZr0.8Y0.2O3-delta.
Titulo: Implications of Cation Interdiffusion between Double Perovskite Cathode and Proton-Conducting Electrolyte for Performance of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Analysis of the element distribution along the cross sections of diffusion couples RBaCo2O6-delta(R = Gd, Pr)|BaZr0.8Y0.2O3-delta showed strong interdiffusion of cations, with cobalt being the most mobile one.
Titulo: Implications of Cation Interdiffusion between Double Perovskite Cathode and Proton-Conducting Electrolyte for Performance of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Its diffusion depth in the electrolyte reaches up to several hundreds of micrometers.
Titulo: Implications of Cation Interdiffusion between Double Perovskite Cathode and Proton-Conducting Electrolyte for Performance of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The addition of NiO as a sintering aid to BaZr0.8Y0.2O3-delta promotes cation diffusion especially through the grain boundary mechanism, increasing the diffusion depth of Co.
Titulo: Implications of Cation Interdiffusion between Double Perovskite Cathode and Proton-Conducting Electrolyte for Performance of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The possible implications of cation interdiffusion on the performance of proton-conducting SOFCs are discussed based on the results obtained.
Titulo: Implications of Cation Interdiffusion between Double Perovskite Cathode and Proton-Conducting Electrolyte for Performance of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
